childs.comment: Default tag used for all the actions.
childs.name: INVALID_TAG

childs.comment: Return true if the action has finished
childs.name: isDone

childs.comment:
Called after the action has finished. It will set the 'target' to nil.
IMPORTANT: You should never call "Action::stop()" manually. Instead, use: "target->stopAction(action);".
childs.name: invalidate

childs.comment: Called every frame with it's delta time, dt in seconds. DON'T override unless you know what you are doing
childs.name: step

childs.comment:
Called once per frame. time a value between 0 and 1.

For example:
- 0 Means that the action just started.
- 0.5 Means that the action is in the middle.
- 1 Means that the action is over.

@param time A value between 0 and 1.
childs.name: update

childs.comment: Called before the action start. It will also set the target
childs.name: startWithTarget

childs.comment:
The "target".
The target will be set with the 'startWithTarget' method.
When the 'stop' method is called, target will be set to nil.
The target is 'assigned', it is not 'retained'.
childs.name: _target

childs.comment: The action tag. An identifier of the action.
childs.name: _tag
Speed

childs.comment:
@class DelayTime
@brief Delays the action a certain amount of seconds.
childs.name: DelayTime
